text:
As announced by Dan at the WIM event last week, this is (to our knowledge) the first time a female faculty panel has been held for the Marriott School. #bigdeal 

This has been a dream in the making and is open to all students in the Marriott School. The MBA will also be hosting a recruiting booth at the event- please invite anyone interested in the program too! 

The five faculty on the panel are:
Dean Madrian, Dean of the Marriott School
Bonnie Anderson, Associate Dean
McKenzie Rees, Organizational Behavior/Management Professor
Bekki Brau, Global Supply Chain Professor
Hannah Judd, Accounting Professor
#powerhouses 

And yes- there will be food. :relaxed: We would love to have as many MBAs as possible! 

Register now and submit questions for the panel here: 
<https://marriott.byu.edu/event/femalepanel2023|https://marriott.byu.edu/event/femalepanel2023>

text:
Hey Everyone! There will be companies with full-time and internship opportunities at this networking event tomorrow Oct 24th at 6pm in the Hinckley Building East Conference room. We are inviting all past MBA SCA Alumni and friends of the program that what to see BYU MBA's get into strategy or consulting roles!

Consulting Companies committed: *McKinsey, Bain, PwC, Slalom, Cicero, Clozd* (looking to get more to come)
Strategy Roles/Companies Committed: *Bill, Dees Limited, School Leadership Alliance, Henry Schein One, Security Metrics, BYU TV* (looking to get more to come)

If you are interested in Consulting it will be a great opportunity!

If you are interested in Strategic roles or strategy roles this will be a great opportunity!

*Many of these companies are looking for interns and full-time roles or have connections to opportunities!*

There will be a soda bar and Hors d'oeuvres
*NOW FREE for everyone - we have decided to drop the fee (thank you, anonymous supporter)*
Business Casual
